In the 3 studies described above (Space Shuttle, ISS, normative), 3 or more measurements of OCR were obtained for each angle of tilt. For all the tests performed on the ground (astronauts, normative population), the OCR amplitudes of each of the subjects’ 3 trials were averaged for each of the body or head tilt angles. An asymmetry ratio was calculated to compare OCR during right and left tilts:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
