				\begin{document}$${\rm{Asymmetry}}\,{\rm{ratio}}=|({\rm{OCR}}\,{\rm{right}}-{\rm{OCR}}\,{\rm{left}})/({\rm{OCR}}\,{\rm{right}}+{\rm{OCR}}\,{\rm{left}})|\times 100$$\end{document}Asymmetryratio=|(OCRright−OCRleft)/(OCRright+OCRleft)|×100Analyses of variance (ANOVAs) were used to compare values of OCR amplitude and asymmetry after whole body tilt and head tilt, and to compare values during sessions (preflight, in-flight, post-flight). Tests of distribution and homogeneity of variances were also performed to check the normality assumption for ANOVAs.
